I used Docker with CI/CD to automate build and deployment of my application.

Whenever code was pushed to GitHub, the CI/CD pipeline was triggered.
In the CI phase, the application was built and tested. Then a Docker image was created using the Dockerfile.

This image was pushed to a container registry like Docker Hub.

In the CD phase, the latest image was pulled from the registry and deployed as a container on the server. This ensured that the same environment was used in development, testing, and production.”

🎯 Pipeline Flow (Very Important)
Developer pushes code → GitHub
CI tool triggers (like Jenkins / GitHub Actions)
Build application
Run tests
Build Docker image
Push image to Docker Hub
Deploy container on server
🎯 Example (GitHub Actions – Simple)
name: CI/CD Pipeline

on: [push]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v2

      - name: Build Docker Image
        run: docker build -t myapp .

      - name: Push to Docker Hub
        run: docker push myapp
